Bauchi metropolis stand still as thousands of supporters trooped to the state capital from across the 20 LGAs to receive the state governor Bala Mohammed following his victory at the Supreme Court. Major roads in the state capital were besieged, causing gridlock for hours. LEADERSHIP reports that a drive of about 20 minutes from the Abubakar Tafawa Balewa International Airport to the state capital took the crowd 3 and half hours to enter the metropolis. The crowd blocked major roads jubilating following the apex court verdict that quashed the prayers of the opposition APC and its candidate Mohammed Abubakar. Thousands of women and youth turned out in large numbers chanting songs of solidarity and bashing the ex-governor, Mr Mohammed. “We are grateful to God for affirming Bala as our governor, we would have cried had the ex-governor came back”, said Saudat Mohammed who left her house chores to celebrate Bala’s victory. Another supporter, Ishaq Mohammed said “my prayers is that may Allah help this governor to deliver on the huge promises he took. “We don’t want Buhari’s like celebration that saw us killing ourselves and got nothing in return”, he added. The governor could not reach government house as at 6pm since he landed at the airport by 2pm because of the crowd.